The paper deals with the problem of sparse recovery in underdetermined systems of linear equations, which is a common topic in several subfields of computer science. However, the focus on the use of a matrix coherency graph to improve the performance of sparse coding algorithms suggests that the paper is most likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) subcategories. Additionally, the use of sparse coding in computer vision (cs.CV) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) also makes these subcategories likely. Finally, the mention of the structure of the dictionary suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) subcategory.
